Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Mix the butter with the nuts and sugar until well combined. Add the flour and the vanilla and mix. Rolling about a tablespoon of dough in your hand, form a half moon or crescent shape. Bake cookies on ungreased cookie sheets at 325 degrees F (165 degrees C) for 15 minutes. Immediately remove from cookie sheets and roll in white sugar.